Note:
Runa Standard Library: Concurrency and Threading Support

Provides comprehensive concurrency and threading support including threads, processes, async operations, synchronization primitives, and parallel processing.

Idiomatic Runa code uses natural language operators:
  Let thread be create thread with function as "worker_function"
  Let process be start process with command as "python script.py"
  Let future be run async with function as "async_task"
  Let result be wait for future to complete

For advanced/AI-generated code, use helpers:
  Let result be create with function as thread_function and args as arguments
  Let result be start with process as proc and wait as wait_mode
:End Note

Process called "create_thread" that takes function as String and args as List[Any] returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Return create_thread_object(function, args)

Process called "start_thread" that takes thread as Dictionary[String, Any] returns Boolean:
    Return start_thread_execution(thread)

